item.description:
I once encountered an interview question that had completely bamboozled me at the time:
&ldquo;Suppose you have a sequence \(X = {X_1, &hellip;, X_N}\) of independently and identically distributed random variables drawn from the same unknown distribution. How would you estimate the variance of the sample median?&rdquo;
In retrospect, the answer seems fairly obvious, but at the time I froze up. As a form of self-atonement, I wanted to answer this question in detail.
